# Playwright Library | Playwright

Playwright module provides a method to launch a browser instance.

## Properties

### chromium
This object can be used to launch or connect to Chromium, returning instances of Browser.

### firefox
This object can be used to launch or connect to Firefox.

### webkit
This object can be used to launch or connect to WebKit.

### devices
Returns a dictionary of devices to be used with browser.newContext() or browser.newPage().

### errors
Playwright methods might throw errors if they are unable to fulfill a request.

```typescript
try {
  await page.locator('.foo').waitFor();
} catch (e) {
  if (e instanceof playwright.errors.TimeoutError) {
    // Handle timeout
  }
}
```

### request
Exposes API that can be used for the Web API testing.

## Best Practices from Documentation:
1. Use specific locators (getByRole, getByText) instead of CSS selectors
2. Handle TimeoutError for async operations
3. Use devices for mobile emulation
4. Close browser instances after tests
5. Use request for API testing

## Error Handling
- Playwright methods throw errors on failure
- Specific error classes available via playwright.errors
- Always handle TimeoutError for wait operations
- Use try-catch for error assertions

## Version: Playwright 1.56.x
Source: https://playwright.dev/docs/api/class-playwright
